properties.headline: Winter Weather Advisory issued January 10 at 11:08PM CST until January 11 at 6:00PM CST by NWS Des Moines IA
properties.description:
...Winter Storm Tonight into Late Saturday...

.A large low pressure system will continue to affect Iowa tonight
into the weekend spreading two episodes of wintry precipitation
across the state. The first push has brought snow and blowing
snow through central sections with freezing rain and a wintry mix
south so far this evening, and will continue to exit the area
through the early morning hours across the eastern forecast area.
The second push Saturday will mainly be snow and blowing snow,
ending from west to east during the evening hours. Moderate to
heavy snow storm total accumulations are expected over the
far east and southeastern third to two-thirds of Iowa.

* WHAT...Light to moderate snow expected. Event total snow
accumulations of 2 to 5 inches. Winds gusting as high as 35
mph.

* WHERE...Northeast Iowa.

* WHEN...Until 6 PM CST Saturday. Snow mainly in two episodes,
with the first episode beginning to taper off, and then the
second episode mainly during the day Saturday.

* IMPACTS...Plan on slippery road conditions, especially during
periods of snowfall. Areas of blowing snow could significantly
reduce visibility.
properties.instruction:
Slow down and use caution while traveling.

The latest road conditions for the state you are calling from can
be obtained by calling 5 1 1.

NWSheadline: WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 6 PM CST SATURDAY
